,Recommended,255280,16760931,"Posted: 28 June, 2015",all,shiaakuma,"I thoroughly enjoyed this game!  When I started, I wasn't overly impressed but as the game went on, I got more and more absorbed in the story and by the end I was having a great time.  Or as great a time as you can have as a criminal escaping Alcatraz and his accomplice wife.  There is some freedom of choice that allows you to sort of adjust the likeability-level of your two playable characters (i.e. some choices will make you into a total ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥♥).+Engaging story+Excellent voice acting+Art style is unique (cartoonish but nicely done)+A variety of endings and variations on endings depending on choices made in the game.+Solutions aren't nearly as obscure as some point-and-click adventure games.  There is thankfully no ""combine a jelly bean and a cat to get a TV antenna"" sorts of solutions and I always applaud that (personal opinion that games should challenge without causing unneeded hair-pulling).-Game length is pretty short - I ran through in about 4.5 hours, getting all three main endings. This makes the full price a little steep but sales and bundles make it reasonably priced.-There are places you can get ""stuck"" in progression and have to reload an earlier save (usually when there needs to be an exchange between the switchable characters that is somewhat order-of-events sensitive)There are a few things to keep in mind about this one:1.  It is definitely NOT for anyone who is squeamish about violence and sexual acts.  There isn't a lot of it, and what there is isn't graphically explicit, but there are some sound effects that might bother the more prudish consumer.2.  This takes place in the 1950s and the slang, including racial slang, reflects that.  It is not ""politically correct"" because there was no such thing back then.  There is also heavy emphasis on the ""Beat"" culture of that time period, including slang, which might sound very strange if you're not too aquainted with 1950s-era hipsters.3. $19.99 is a little pricey for the length of the game, so you might want to get it on sale or in a bundle.  Daedelic makes some great games so almost any of their bundles probably includes some games that are even better than this one."
