,Recommended,255280,31092905,Posted: 12 April,all,Igor the Viking,"Getting past the technical issues, this is a point-and-click gemI'll start with the cons: Several people complained about achievements not popping up in windows 10, so before I started playing at my own risk, I decided to follow a community guide to a ""safe"" mode to avoid complications. These fixes include running the game in compatibility mode, running it as administrator and using windowed mode. It isn't complex, but worth mentioning in my review. Specially the ""windowed mode"" part, which I know can be a deal breaker for some.Getting past that, the game itself is great, the puzzles are usually fluid and very logical (when compared to many other games), the story is engaging and never felt boring (at least for me). I still got stuck a couple times, but during most of the gameplay, finding your next action is straight-forward and yet it still feels rewarding when you ""make the story go forward"". Being able to go back and forth between the 2 characters is a nice feature and the change of atmosphere contributes to keeping things fresh. There is even a (not very deep) ""decisions matter"" system and a small branch of choices at the end. Recommended."
