,Recommended,255280,31313503,Posted: 22 April,all,Awesome Possum,"Not an overly complex point-and-click. Most of my ""play time"" was actually AFK making dinner, cleaning, forgetting I even had the game open time. There are no real puzzles. The story was kinda cute. The characters are certainly characters. The open-mindedness of the beatniks despite their era is refreshing. At times, the graphics are a little wonky, though not terrible. The music is pleasant, the voice acting is very natural.I like that there are some choices to make, though there are seemingly no real consequences for those different choices -- unless you're an achievement hunter (which I am, and I'm surprised at how few I obtained in one playthrough). In the end, there are two endings, one of which makes little sense. I mean, the idea of it makes sense; the execution doesn't.If you are an achievement hunter, I suggest using a guide or walkthrough.Comparing this to all the other Daedalic titles I've played, I'd say this was probably the lowest budget one. Still not too shabby, given that fact. Buy it on sale. It'll be a nice relaxing game for a couple nights of entertainment."
